## 12. Document Index (4 Core Files)

> Principle: minimum files, maximum context. Do not create additional doc files without a clear reason.

| File | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `.cursorrules` | Tech stack, conventions, business logic, hard rules (this file) |
| `docs/progress.md` | Current dev status, known bugs, **User Stories** (no separate `story.md` needed) |
| `docs/architecture/[feature].md` | Deep-dive design for a specific feature (e.g. `rewards.md`, `investments.md`) |
| `docs/decisions.md` | Architecture Decision Records (ADR format) — what was decided and why |
| `docs/SUPABASE_SCHEMA.md` | **Authoritative** DDL for all tables, indexes, RLS policies, RPC functions |

User Stories are written directly inside `progress.md` under `## Story: <name>` headings.
`docs/architecture/database.md` is superseded by `docs/SUPABASE_SCHEMA.md` for schema details;
keep only relationship diagrams and design rationale in the architecture file.

